        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(pdf): guard native provider requests",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nRoute native Anthropic/Gemini PDF provider requests through OpenClaw's shared guarded provider HTTP path.\n\nRelated: NVIDIA-dev/openclaw-tracking#786\n\n## Changes\n\n- Use `resolveProviderHttpRequestConfig` and `postJsonRequest` for native PDF provider POSTs.\n- Thread resolved model headers and provider request transport metadata from the PDF tool into native PDF helpers.\n- Replace successful provider `res.json()` parsing with bounded `readProviderJsonResponse` parsing.\n- Add focused regressions for private-network blocking, explicit `allowPrivateNetwork` opt-in, and oversized successful JSON responses.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `corepack pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/tools/pdf-native-providers.test.ts src/agents/tools/pdf-tool.test.ts`\n- `corepack pnpm format:check -- src/agents/tools/pdf-native-providers.ts src/agents/tools/pdf-tool.ts src/agents/tools/pdf-native-providers.test.ts`\n- `corepack pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --parallel-tests \"node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/tools/pdf-native-providers.test.ts src/agents/tools/pdf-tool.test.ts\"` clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\n## Notes\n\n- AI-assisted.\n- No `CHANGELOG.md` update.\n- `corepack pnpm check:changed -- src/agents/tools/pdf-native-providers.ts src/agents/tools/pdf-tool.ts src/agents/tools/pdf-native-providers.test.ts` did not run checks because the delegated Blacksmith Testbox path failed at local `crabbox` binary sanity checks before executing the lane.\n",
